Module kivakit.core.kernel
Package com.telenav.kivakit.core.kernel.language.paths

Class Path<Element extends java.lang.Comparable<Element>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.telenav.kivakit.core.kernel.language.paths.Path<Element>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Countable, Sized, java.lang.Comparable<Path<Element>>, java.lang.Iterable<Element>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    StringPath
    public abstract class Path<Element extends java.lang.Comparable<Element>>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Iterable<Element>, java.lang.Comparable<Path<Element>>, Sized
    Abstraction of an immutable path of elements of a given type with an optional root element.

    Kinds of Paths

    • "" - The empty path (with no elements and no root)
    • "/" - The root path (UNIX)
    • "C:\" - A root path (Windows)
    • "D:\" - A root path (Windows)
    • "/a/b/c" - Absolute path
    • "a/b/c" - Relative path

    Relative and Absolute Paths

    Paths that have a root() element are absolute and isAbsolute() will return true. Any path without a root is a relative path and isRelative() will return true. A root path has a root element but no path elements and isRoot() will return true. The empty path has neither a root nor any elements and isEmpty() will return true.

    Element Retrieval

    • first() - The first element in the path or null if there is none
    • last() - The last element in the path or null if there is none
    • first(int) - The first n elements in the path or null if there are fewer elements
    • last(int) - The last n elements in the path or null if there are fewer elements
    • get(int) - The nth element in the path or null if there is no nth element
    • rootElement() - The root element, if any
    • elements() - The elements in this path
    • iterator() - The elements in this path
    • stream() - A stream of the elements in this path (not including the root)

    Checks

    • isAbsolute() - True if this path has a root element
    • isRelative() - True if this path does not have a root element
    • isEmpty() - True if this path has no root and no elements
    • isRoot() - True if this path has a root element but no path elements
    • endsWith(Path) - True if this path ends with the given path
    • startsWith(Path) - True if this path starts with the given path

    Functional Methods

    The following methods are functional, meaning that they return a copy of the path that is changed in some way while this path itself is not altered. The copy is made with the method copy(), which calls the subclass to create the copy through onCopy(Comparable, List). This allows subclasses to reuse the logic in this class while still dealing in instances of the subclass type.

    • emptyPath() - The empty path
    • parent() - The parent of this path
    • root() - The root path of this path
    • subpath(int start, int end) - The elements from start to end (exclusive)
    • transformed(Function) - This path with each element transformed by the given function
    • #withChild(Element) - This path with the given element appended
    • withChild(Path) - This path with the given path appended
    • #withParent(Element) - This path with the given element prepended
    • withParent(Path) - This path with the given element prepended
    • #withRoot(Element) - This path with the given root element
    • withoutFirst() - This path without any first element or null if there is no first element
    • withoutLast() - This path without any last element or null if there is no last element
    • withoutRoot() - This path without the root element
    • withoutPrefix(Path) - This path without the given prefix path or null if it is not found
    • withoutSuffix(Path) - This path without the given suffix path or null if it is not found
